<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-29T21:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-29T21:42:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/1082: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Collier</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-29T22:00:00-04:42"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            29, 1922—10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:45
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>91. My telegram number 90, November 28, 10 p.m. Protocol ratified
                                without reservations by Chilean Congress in consequence of failure
                                of Senate this afternoon to obtain more than 15 votes for
                                reservations, 14 opposed.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Collier</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>